# Setting up docker image/container
* Windows users need to open docker application before initiaing docker in WSL
* Open WSL and run docker by typing docker Set working directory
```
cd /mnt/d/typology
```
* Build image using environment.yml file
```
docker build -t typology .
```
* Mount and run image (Example)
```
cd /mnt/d/typology
docker run -p 8888:8888 -v $(pwd):/home/gisuser/ -it typology
```
* Exit Container (in WSL) ctrl + C
* Remove containers
```
docker rm $(docker ps -aq)
```